jopt.csp.spi.solver
Class ChoicePointNumArraySet

java.lang.Object
  jopt.csp.spi.solver.ChoicePointNumArraySet
All Implemented Interfaces:
ChoicePointEntry
public class ChoicePointNumArraySet
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChoicePointEntry

ChoicePointNumArraySet maintains a set of numeric stacks that will push and rollback together.

This class is different from ChoicePointDataMap in that it only stores certain types of numeric data. The ChoicePointDataMap is similar but can store any type of data as long as it is an object.

This class is not thread safe.

pop

public void pop()
Description copied from interface: ChoicePointEntry

Restores values in the current entry from data recorded in the internal stack. Any listeners attached to this entry are notified that the values in the entry are about to be rolled back before the action takes place allowing listeners to act accordingly.

This method is more efficient to the popDelta method and is encouraged for use if delta information is not necessary
